 WARNING [pt_PT.po] mismatched patterns: --continue
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] >> msgid:
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] Commands:
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] p, pick <commit> = use commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] r, reword <commit> = use commit, but edit the commit message
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] e, edit <commit> = use commit, but stop for amending
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] s, squash <commit> = use commit, but meld into previous commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] f, fixup <commit> = like "squash", but discard this commit's log message
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] x, exec <command> = run command (the rest of the line) using shell
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] b, break = stop here (continue rebase later with 'git rebase --continue')
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] d, drop <commit> = remove commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] l, label <label> = label current HEAD with a name
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] t, reset <label> = reset HEAD to a label
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] m, merge [-C <commit> | -c <commit>] <label> [# <oneline>]
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] . create a merge commit using the original merge commit's
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] . message (or the oneline, if no original merge commit was
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] . specified). Use -c <commit> to reword the commit message.
 WARNING [pt_PT.po]
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] These lines can be re-ordered; they are executed from top to bottom.
 WARNING [pt_PT.po]
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] >> msgstr:
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] Comandos:
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] p, pick = usar commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] r, reword = usar commit, mas editar a mensagem de commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] e, edit = usar commit, mas parar para emendar
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] s, squash = usar commit, mas fundir com o commit anterior
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] f, fixup = como "squash", mas descartar a mensagem deste commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] x, exec = executar o comando (o resto da linha) usando a shell
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] d, drop = remover commit
 WARNING [pt_PT.po]
 WARNING [pt_PT.po] Estas linhas pode ser reordenadas; são executadas de cima para baixo.
 WARNING [pt_PT.po]
